  "texts": [
    "acc extra is clearly an unbiased estimator of outof-sample accuracy because it never trains on test.",
    "In other words, the expected value of acc extra is the accuracy one would observe on independent, identically distributed data.",
    "4.2 acc test acc test is identical to acc extra, except that taskadaptive pretraining is done on unlabeled text from test instead of extra in step 1. acc test represents what one might see in a competition like RAFT, where pretraining on unlabeled text from test is encouraged.",
    "It is unclear whether this accuracy estimator is unbiased, because it involved pretraining and evaluating on the same set of test set text.",
    "A reasonable hypothesis is that it is overoptimistic, i.e., E[acc test ] > E[acc extra ]."
  ],
